All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ABoard
The ABoard class serves as an abstract base class for different types of Sudoku boards.
AGame
The AGame class is an abstract base class that defines the common interface for different types of Sudoku games.
Board
The Board class represents the game board for the Sudoku puzzle.
Game
The Game class represents a Sudoku game with a 6x6 grid.
GameController
Controller class for managing the game logic and UI interactions.
GameStage
The GameStage class represents the main game window for the Sudoku application.
IBoard
The IBoard interface defines the contract for Sudoku board implementations.
IFields
The IFields interface defines the methods required for managing text fields in the Sudoku application.
IGame
The IGame interface defines the contract for Sudoku game implementations.
ITimer
The ITimer interface defines the methods required for a timer component within the Sudoku application.
Main
The main entry point for the MiniProject2 application.
WelcomeController
The WelcomeController class handles the logic and user interactions for the welcome stage of the Sudoku game.
WelcomeStage
The WelcomeStage class represents the initial welcome window for the Sudoku application.
